content.description: Hard line through pockets up a very steep face. Start low with left hand in a big mouth, and toss to the finger stack pocket. From there do a sequencey sequence up and top out on a sloper about 16' up the right arete. Sharp, scary, bad landing, terrific, transcendent, etc.
content.protection: 3 pads + spotter to keep you off the backbreaker rock.
content.location: Start low, left hand in a good hold.

content.description: This boulder is down the hill from Munge Lunge and to the east. It was blocked by a huge tree but the fire this summer opened up some lines on it. V1 and V2s, just follow the obvious lines straight up and on the left side. On the far left side of the warm up wall is a v4 on thin holds, and the left arete ( sds )is good harder line too. A sketchy sharp hard line call Dry Socket  is on the overhung face around the other way.
